This paper discusses the use of echo state networks, which are a type of recurrent neural network commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on comparing different methods for training the output layer of these networks to classify noisy data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SD (Sound), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these are all areas where echo state networks have been applied in the past.
